{
  "texts": [
    "Carreira et al. (2017) proposed the I3D model in 2017 using the same refinement idea.",
    "The main idea was to extend Inception's 2D model into a 3D model.",
    "I3D can achieve excellent performance after full pre-training in kinetics.",
    "Similarly, Tran et al. proposed a new spatiotemporal convolution module called R(2+1) D in 2018, which approximates the complete three-dimensional convolution with a twodimensional convolution kernel and a one-dimensional convolution, thus separating the processing of space and time.",
    "Lin et al. (2019a) proposed the temporal shift module (TSM) network in 2019."
  ]
}